.TH BUILDBOT 1 "April 2026" "arch\-native" "User Commands"
.\" ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.SH NAME
buildbot \- arch\-native package build daemon and CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B buildbot
.I COMMAND
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B buildbot
.RB [ \-\-config
.IR file ]
.RB [ \-\-debug ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B buildbot
is the daemon and CLI for
.BR arch\-native ,
a self\-hosted build system that rebuilds installed Arch (or Artix) Linux
packages from source with CPU\-optimised compiler flags, signs the resulting
packages with GPG, and publishes them as a local pacman repository.
.PP
Invoked without a
.I COMMAND
it starts the build daemon.
Invoked with a command it runs the CLI and exits immediately.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS status
Show service state, the package currently being built, queue and failure
counts, and stats from the most recent poll cycle.
.SS doctor
Verify that all required paths exist, JSON state files are valid, the GPG
home has correct permissions (0700), and the chroot pacman keyring is
initialised.
Safe to run while the service is active.
.SS built [\-n \fIN\fR]
List packages successfully rebuilt by arch\-native, newest first.
.TP
.BI \-n " N"
Limit output to the
.I N
most recent entries (default: all).
.SS logs \fIPKG\fR [\-f]
Print the latest build log for
.IR PKG .
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-follow
Follow the log in real time (equivalent to
.BR "tail \-f" ).
Useful while a build is in progress.
.SS queue [\-n \fIN\fR]
List the pending build queue.
.TP
.BI \-n " N"
Limit output to the first
.I N
entries (default: 25).
.SS failed [\-n \fIN\fR]
List failed builds with failure reason and retry count.
.TP
.BI \-n " N"
Limit output to the first
.I N
entries (default: all).
.SS retry \fIPKG\fR [\-\-all] [\-\-dry\-run]
Re\-queue failed package(s) for another build attempt.
Requires the service to be stopped first.
.TP
.B \-\-all
Re\-queue every failed package.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be re\-queued without writing.
.SS clear \fIPKG\fR [\-\-all] [\-\-dry\-run]
Remove package(s) from the failed list without re\-queuing them.
Requires the service to be stopped first.
.TP
.B \-\-all
Clear the entire failed list.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be cleared without writing.
.SS sync [\-\-reset] [\-\-dry\-run]
Diff the installed package list against
.I built.json
and queue any new or updated packages.
Requires the service to be stopped first.
.TP
.B \-\-reset
Clear the existing queue first, then rebuild from scratch.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be queued without writing.
.SS init
Initialise a new arch\-native installation: create the directory layout
under
.IR /var/lib/arch\-native/ ,
build the clean devtools chroot, initialise the pacman keyring, and
generate the GPG signing key.
Safe to re\-run \(em skips steps already complete.
.SS "patch {create|show|check} \fIPKG\fR"
Manage local PKGBUILD patches stored in
.IR /var/lib/arch\-native/pkgbuilds/local/ .
.TP
.BI "patch create " PKG " [\-\-force]"
Resolve the upstream PKGBUILD for
.I PKG
(using
.BR repo_priority ),
open it in
.BR $EDITOR ,
and save the diff as a local patch.
.B \-\-force
overwrites an existing patch with a fresh copy of upstream.
.TP
.BI "patch show " PKG
Print the local patch for
.IR PKG .
.TP
.BI "patch check " "PKG " | " \-\-all"
Verify that the local patch for
.I PKG
(or all patches with
.BR \-\-all )
still applies cleanly against the current upstream PKGBUILD.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-config " file"
Path to the configuration file.
Default:
.IR /etc/arch\-native.conf .
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable verbose (DEBUG\-level) logging.
Daemon mode only.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/arch\-native.conf
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /var/lib/arch\-native/built.json
Record of every package successfully rebuilt, with version and timestamp.
.TP
.I /var/lib/arch\-native/pending.json
The build queue.
.TP
.I /var/lib/arch\-native/failed.json
Packages that failed to build, with failure reason and retry count.
.TP
.I /var/lib/arch\-native/in_progress.json
Package currently being built; re\-inserted at the front of the queue on
daemon restart for crash recovery.
.TP
.I /var/lib/arch\-native/metrics.json
Last\-cycle statistics (succeeded, failed, skipped counts and timestamps).
.TP
.I /var/lib/arch\-native/logs/<pkg>/
Per\-package build logs, one file per build attempt.
LTO\-retry runs are saved as
.IR YYYYMMDD\-HHMMSS\-nolto.log .
.TP
.I /var/lib/arch\-native/pkgbuilds/local/<pkg>/<pkg>.patch
Local PKGBUILD patches managed by
.BR "buildbot patch" .
.SH EXAMPLES
Check the current build state:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
buildbot status
.EE
.RE
.PP
Follow the build log for firefox as it builds:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
buildbot logs firefox \-f
.EE
.RE
.PP
Re\-queue a single failed package:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
sudo systemctl stop arch\-native
sudo buildbot retry networkmanager
sudo systemctl start arch\-native
.EE
.RE
.PP
Rebuild the pending queue after a large package sync:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
sudo systemctl stop arch\-native
sudo buildbot sync \-\-reset
sudo systemctl start arch\-native
.EE
.RE
.PP
Create a local patch to fix a build failure:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
sudo buildbot patch create xvidcore
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pacman (8),
.BR makechrootpkg (1),
.BR makepkg (8),
.BR repo\-add (8),
.BR arch\-native.conf (5)
